                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="106197" author="springuser007" created="Thu, 24 Jul 2014 06:50:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you. I been waiting for this. Here is the ticket I opened earlier &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-244&quot; title=&quot;SDR Schema follows json-schema?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAREST-244&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAREST-244&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="111152" author="springuser007" created="Tue, 6 Jan 2015 08:42:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this feature expected in Fowler release?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="112318" author="olivergierke" created="Fri, 6 Feb 2015 04:06:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve just pushed a revamped version of our JSON Schema support to the feature branch for this ticket (consume via the dependency version &lt;tt&gt;2.3.0.&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATAREST-354&quot; title=&quot;Revamp JSON Schema support to current draft of the spec&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DATAREST-354&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DATAREST-354&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-SNAPSHOT&lt;/tt&gt;) that hopefully improves the general situation by quite a bit. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-data-rest/commit/0b2cdd0798909bfe6c897d64e1c33d81ed002e19&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;this commit&lt;/a&gt; for details.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve linked all related tickets I could find together as they mention aspects that might have been touched by the commit or get into this ticket, too. Please give the snapshots a try and report findings. If all goes well we might be able to get the current state into Fowler RC1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What I&apos;d still like to look into a bit deeper is the possibility to pick up more customizations made to the serialization through Jackson mixins or serializers out of the box. There currently is a configuration API to register custom formats and patterns for a type but they effectively duplicate stuff that&apos;s customized on the &lt;tt&gt;ObjectMapper&lt;/tt&gt; already.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
